Example of the underwater adaptation of the popular arduino shield for ultrasonic rangefinder. 

Cable will be mounted through Tupperware base using epoxy or resin. 

Module requires 10 microsecond pulse to be sent to its trigger pin. 
Releases 8 pulses and measures time of flight to determine distances.
Averages and returns a distance. Blind below 5cm and maximum range is 50cm.
Read from the ECHO pin. 

